    <texts>
      <txt c="X" a="X" r="X" s="2" w="850" x="40" y="80" delay="0" pt="1" e="-3" align="left">The ship is running behind schedule when she enters the port. There is a long queue for ships waiting to get their goods cleared by Customs officials. The local officials quickly learn that the ship is running behind schedule and offer the Captain the chance to jump the line. The Captain pays.

What would this payment be considered to be?</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="200" delay="0" crct="71" align="left">A bribe</txt>
      <txt c="X" s="2" y="260" delay="0" crct="31" align="left">A facilitation payment</txt>
